ss black hole are unlikely to account for the implied\nluminosity. We further argue that the strength of the hard emission in these\nsources and well-established phenomena frequently observed in stellar-mass\nblack holes near to the Eddington limit suggest that optically-thick\nphotospheres are unlikely to be the origin of the cool thermal emission in\nbright ULXs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Oct 2003 16:24:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 18 Mar 2004 21:46:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-09-17"}
