y\nof anomalous Cepheids in dwarf spheroidal galaxies correlates with the mean\nmetallicity of their parent galaxy, and that the Andromeda II and Andromeda VI\nanomalous Cepheids appear to follow the same relation as those in the Galactic\ndwarf spheroidals.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Oct 2003 18:56:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
